data.description: Welcome to 388 Boush Street in desirable Downtown. This sophisticated condo offers both style and location featuring a spacious and welcoming open layout with hardwood flooring, high ceilings, and a wall of windows overlooking the tree-lined streets of Historic Freemason. The open living room and kitchen are ideal for entertaining with a fashionable Chef’s kitchen with Quartz countertops, wonderful cabinet space, and island with seating. The primary bedroom is very large with a sizeable walk-in closet and stunning updated bath with walk-in shower. The second bedroom features a Murphy Bed and custom built-ins. Additional features include updated second bath, great closet space, pantry, in unit washer & dryer, storage space, secure front door, and an attached city parking garage. Perfectly located just a few blocks to the Elizabeth River Trail, Granby Street, EVMS, Sentara, and Norfolk’s waterfront.
